content:
You can use a calculated insight to define and calculate multidimensional metrics on your entire digital state in Data Cloud. You can create metrics at the profile, segment, and population levels.

Marketers can use metrics, dimensions, and filters to define segment criteria and personalization attributes for activation. Data analysts can also visualize the insights in CRM Analytics to understand data patterns.

Calculated insights can help you understand each stage of the customer journey by analyzing various metrics. Here are some benefits:

* Build metrics on large-scale data in Data Cloud using analytical functions for in-depth analysis.
* Analyze streaming data in near real-time using streaming insights and calculate metrics based on a user-defined time frame for streaming data.
* Calculate custom metrics using complex logic, mathematics, statistics, time series functions, and complex workflows.

You can create a calculated insight using SQL or Builder. Calculated Insights List View allows you to see the details and edit your record from the list view.

The processing and retention times for a calculated insight depend on the amount of data in the underlying data model objects (DMOs) and the time dimensions used in Data Cloud. You can specify the frequency, start date, and time to process a calculated insight.

Calculated insights feature availability varies across Data Cloud. Formulas, operators, and calculated insights allow you to create audiences in different ways and at different stages of your workflow.

You can save, edit, clone, and process a calculated insight manually in Data Cloud. Autopopulated join keys make it easy to connect engagement data with a unified profile. You can schedule a calculated insight to control when to process it and keep it up to date with data changes.

Use a calculated insight to control data-driven insights in segmentation. You can also describe the calculated insight's metrics and dimensions in a segmentation filter.
title: Calculated Insights and Metrics in Salesforce Data Cloud
